


Project Overview: File System Recovery & Optimization Tool
This is a complete, production-ready file system simulator implementing advanced OS concepts like inode-based storage, space allocation strategies, caching, crash recovery, and optimization. Built in pure Python (no external deps except optional Flask), with both CLI and web frontends.

Core Backend Components (6 modules)
Module	Purpose	Key Features
filesystem_core.py	Inode/block foundation	Metadata tracking, checksums, integrity
free_space_manager.py	Disk allocation	First/Best/Worst Fit, bitmap, defrag
directory_manager.py	Hierarchy	Create/list/navigate/search dirs/files
file_access_optimizer.py	Performance	LRU cache, read-ahead, access analysis
recovery_manager.py	Disaster recovery	Checkpoints, crash sim, repair, recovery
disk_simulator.py	Integration	Unified API, stats, JSON export/import
User Interfaces
Interactive CLI (main.py)

Menu-driven (files/dirs/recovery/optimize/stats/demos)
Demo scenarios (normal ops, crash recovery, optimization)
Run: python main.py
Flask Web Backend (web_app.py)

REST API for all operations
Session-based simulators
Endpoints: /api/file/create, /api/crash/simulate, /api/optimize, etc.
Run: python web_app.py (localhost:5000)
React/Vite Frontend (frontend/)

Modern SPA dashboard
Real-time stats, operations feed
Proxies to Flask API
Run: cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev (localhost:5173)
Legacy Flask Dashboard (templates/dashboard.html + static/)

Server-rendered UI fallback
Testing & Examples
test_suite.py: 8 categories (ops, allocation, cache, recovery, etc.) – python test_suite.py
usecases.py: 6 real-world scenarios (DB backup, logs, media, migration, frag recovery, tuning)
Key Capabilities
File Ops: Create/read/write/delete with caching
Space Mgmt: 3 strategies, fragmentation analysis/defrag
Recovery: Checkpoints, crash simulation (light/moderate/severe), auto-repair
Perf: LRU cache (hit rates), access patterns, optimization
Stats: Blocks used/free, frag ratio, cache efficiency
Persistence: JSON state export/import
Quick Demo Commands

# CLI Demo
python main.py  # → Option 9 for demos

# Full Stack Web
python web_app.py &  # Terminal 1: Backend
cd frontend && npm run dev  # Terminal 2: React UI → localhost:5173

# Tests
python test_suite.py  # All pass ✓

# Use Cases
python usecases.py
Architecture Flow

CLI/React → DiskSimulator → [Core Modules] → Inodes/Blocks/Bitmap/Cache
                          ↓
                       Stats/Recovery/Optimize
Total: ~3,000 LOC, fully tested, documented (README.md, MODULE_INDEX.md, QUICKSTART.md, PROJECT_SUMMARY.txt). Ready for demos/presentations.

